                                <div class="text-center pt-3 pb-5" style="padding-left: 7rem; padding-right:7rem;">

                                    A newborn with Classic Galactosemia will experience life-threatening <strong>complications within days</strong> after ingesting breast milk or a lactose-containing formula. Without dietary galactose restriction,
                                    manifestations of Galactosemia include: feeding problems, failure to thrive, liver damage, lethargy, seizures, and sepsis (mostly <i>E. coli</i>).<sup>1,3</sup>

                                </div>

                            </div>
